### Decision 4 — The mis-tagged `retro-workflow-workflow-*` retros

7 of the 10 workflow-scope retros carry `trigger=cadence-retro` but have NO subjects
and a commit-sha title (`... — commit a568056`). They are arguably mis-tagged
(workflow retros, not cohort cadence) — but **this bead explicitly DEFERS re-tagging
them.** Justification:
- Re-tagging is a data re-capture identical in kind to the 8hq.5 sidecar backfill, and
  these refs are pre-cutoff WARN material there already (check (f)); folding it in here
  would blow the subjects-only scope fence.
- The guard (g) is designed so it does NOT false-positive on them: their titles have
  no parseable `(a/b/c)` id-list, so check (g) SKIPS them ("where possible"). VERIFIED
  by the corpus dry-run — all 7 are reported SKIP, zero WARNs.
- So the guard does NOT silently pass them by accident; it correctly has nothing to
  assert because they make no in-title subject claim. The plan STATES this explicitly
  rather than relying on luck. If a future decision wants them re-tagged to
  `trigger=process-retro` (matching the 3 sibling workflow retros at
  refs/.../215650Z/215651Z/215702Z), that is a separate backfill bead.

